         <abstract>
            <p>The computation of the exponential integral &lt;latex&gt;$\mathrm{Ei}(x), x &gt; 0$&lt;/latex&gt;, using rational Chebyshev approximations is discussed. The necessary approximations are presented in well-conditioned forms for the intervals (0, 6], [6, 12], [12, 24] and [24, ∞). Maximal relative errors are as low as from 8 × 10&lt;sup&gt;-19&lt;/sup&gt; to 2 × 10&lt;sup&gt;-21&lt;/sup&gt;. In addition, the value of the zero of Ei(x) is presented to 30 decimal places.</p>
          </abstract>
